metadata.name: Equilibrium
metadata.description:
From our eternal glaciers
Those who inhabit us
And those that bring to melt
Of crystal clear sadness
Our indifferent hearts,
To the beauty of a tree
An olive branch will be born
No
An olive tree in all its splendor
Taking root
Reaching our wrecks
Its palms will call
Of their sweet twinkling
The dove that returns
To bloom the air 
With the noise of its beak
Against the green fruit
And its woody core

The world will become again
What it is:
A dreamy foliage
On the surface of the water
